    <section class="security" id="security">
      <div class="wrap security-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Security model</span>
          <h2>Keep the route private because the host surface is real.</h2>
          <p>
            Sidemesh can expose agent transcripts, approvals, workspace files,
            terminal access, forwarded ports, and previews. That power is the
            point. It is also why public internet exposure should not be the
            default.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="route-lines" aria-label="Private network route diagram">
